The paper describes the development and testing of a machine-learned model for real-time detection of foodborne illness using web search and location data. This involves the use of artificial intelligence (AI) and machine learning (ML) techniques to analyze large amounts of data and identify patterns that can be used to detect potential outbreaks of foodborne illness. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). 

The paper also involves the use of information retrieval (IR) techniques to analyze web search data, which suggests that cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is another likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of cryptographic techniques to protect the privacy of users' data, which suggests that cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the application of ML techniques to public health, which suggests that cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is another possible sub-category.
